[0.000, "o", "    \u001b[1;34m\"body\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;32m\"`ellipsis[:maxWidth]` slices the UTF-8 bytes of \\\"…\\\". For `maxWidth == 1` this returns an invalid UTF-8 string (first byte only), and for `maxWidth < 0` it will panic. Consider guarding at the top with `if maxWidth <= 0 { return \\\"\\\" }` and, when you need a 1-cell ellipsis, return the full ellipsis rune (not a byte slice) so output remains valid UTF-8 in these small-width branches.\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[1;34m\"originalLine\"\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m:\u001b[0m \u001b[0;39m105\u001b[0m\u001b[1;39m,\u001b[0m\r\n"]
